Both sides of the panini on my vegetable panini sandwich were burned black.  When I returned the sandwich for a new one, the top part of the replacement wasn't burned but the cheese inside wasn't melted and the bottom panini was the same bottom as the one I'd returned -- burned black.  They'd obviously replaced the filling and just the top of the panini and left the bottom of the original one untouched.  Very dishonest.  They thought I wouldn't check the bottom.  A staff member (I don't know her name or title) told me the press they use to make panini sandwiches has to burn the panini or else the cheese in the filling won't melt!  Yes, she admitted this to me. And the staff was obviously annoyed that I had the nerve to refuse to eat burned-black panini.  I'd say they need a new method of preparing a panini sandwich.  I won't be returning.  BTW, many chefs and cooks these days seem to think it's fine to burn bread.  Some customers might accept their bread blackened, but I can't stand burned food of any kind.  Another complaint about Corner Bakery Cafe:  I read the ingredients list on some of their baked goods and discovered that artificial preservatives are used in everything.  I was going to buy some of the baked goods, which looked appealing, but was turned off by the use of preservatives, so I didn't buy any.  And one final complaint:  The menu says each sandwich comes with a pickle and bakery chips, neither of which I received.  I didn't realize until reading the menu online right now that I was supposed to get them with the panini.  So that's three strikes -- and Corner Bakery Cafe is out for me.  P.S. Since I wrote this review, the owner replied online, asking me to give him additional information on a form whose address he included.  I replied on that form -- and have heard nothing back from him!  So while the owner may sound sympathetic in these Google reviews, he suggests that he'll "make good" but then never does.

I hope it my experience is an isolated incident as my experience was terrible. However, the staff were extremely friendly. I set up catering for 10 out of state colleagues a week prior. Needless to say, the first day that my order was to be delivered at 11:30 AM, it was superbly late. I called the store several times in regards to my order and was  disconnected (hung up on) each time. After an hour, I called again and spoke to several individuals after being placed on hold several times to get to someone in the catering department. After 5 minutes of conversation,  I was informed that my order was never placed into the system for delivery. I was told the order would be processed and delivered within 20 minutes. Though the delivery fee was waived, it still took another hour for the delivery to occur. Moreover, I was given conflicting information regarding the invoices which were to be emailed to me. The invoices were never emailed to me. Therefore, after the second day, I canceled the rest of the orders and found another caterer. As I stated, I hope this was an isolated incident. However, if not,  I hope they get it together soon for the next catering order.
